Dear all,

this is a reminder for the workshop

   Geometry in Modal Homotopy Type Theory

at

   Carnegie Mellon University, Pittsburgh

taking place

   March 11-15, 2019

PLEASE NOTE: The deadline for registration has been extended until the end
of the week and there is now a list of participants on the workshop's
website.

Homotopy Type Theory (HoTT) is one of the tools to reason within a
higher topos. The recent extensions of HoTT by modalities has led to
stronger relations to the use of higher toposes in Topology,
Differential Geometry and Algebraic Geometry. This workshop is about the
development of Modal HoTT and its applications to Geometry.
The invited speakers are:

   Peter Arndt
   Ulrik Buchholtz
   Eric Finster
   Egbert Rijke
   Urs Schreiber
   Mike Shulman

For more information, see:

http://www.andrew.cmu.edu/user/fwellen/modal-workshop.html

All the best,

Felix Wellen


